data.description: In Joplin, Missouri, on February 26, 2026, Missouri Southern State University (MSSU) marked a significant moment with the inauguration of the Public Safety and Forensics Institute. This event signifies a major advancement in law enforcement and forensic science education for the region.

data.title: Aura Minerals Inc. declares a dividend of US$0.66 per share based on Q4 2025 results, resulting in a dividend yield of 6.2%.
data.description: Aura Minerals Inc., based in Road Town, British Virgin Islands, made an announcement on Feb. 26, 2026, declaring a dividend of US$0.66 per common share, totaling approximately US$55.12 million. This amount exceeds the minimum outlined in the Company's Dividend Policy. As per the policy, Aura may distribute quarterly cash dividends up to 20% of its reported Adjusted EBITDA for the respective three-month period, after deducting sustaining and exploration capital expenditures for that period. The company's Board of Directors approved this dividend payment. Aura Minerals is listed on Nasdaq under the symbol AUGO and on B3 under AURA33.

data.description: Vitalik Buterin has detailed a plan to gradually replace four risky elements of Ethereum's cryptographic structure.

data.title: AHF sues FL Health Dept to block rule cutting HIV drug access for thousands in Fort Lauderdale.
data.description: A lawsuit has been filed by AHF against the Florida Health Department in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. The lawsuit aims to prevent the implementation of an emergency rule that would limit access to HIV medication for thousands of individuals. The rule is set to impact a significant number of people who rely on these medications for their health.

data.title: Summit unveils 1229 Hydraulic Crane with 205-pound weight decrease in 12,000-pound capacity class, stows 3 times faster.
data.description: A new hydraulic crane, the 1229 model, is set to revolutionize the 12,000-pound capacity class with advanced ASE Phase 5 intelligence and a weight reduction of 205 pounds. This innovative crane, introduced by Summit Truck Bodies, boasts a significantly faster stowage time compared to conventional systems, stowing three times quicker. The company, headquartered in the United States, unveiled this groundbreaking technology at a showcase in Las Vegas on February 26, 2026.

data.title: Sunoco LP announced an upsized private offering of $600 million for 5.375% senior notes due in 2031 and 5.625% notes due in 2034.
data.description: Dallas-based Sunoco LP (NYSE: SUN) recently revealed it has successfully priced a private offering of senior notes due in 2031 and 2034. The offering, totaling $1.2 billion, consists of 5.375% senior notes amounting to $600 million due in 2031 and 5.625% senior notes totaling $600 million due in 2034. The initial offering size of $500 million was upsized to meet the demands of the market.

data.title: Brandi AI introduces GEO Framework for AI visibility: SEO, AEO, and GEO layers for brand optimization in search.
data.description: A new AI framework named Brandi has been introduced to provide clarity on Search Engine Optimization (SEO), Answer Engine Optimization (AEO), and Generative Engine Optimization (GEO). These elements are outlined as sequential layers within a unified AI visibility system for brands in the digital space. The updated approach emphasizes the importance of adapting to AI-driven algorithms for improved online presence. Key Takeaways include the shift in search priorities from rankings towards a more comprehensive strategy integrating various optimization techniques.

data.title: Commerce Media Tech partners with IPinfo to adopt accuracy-first IP data in AdTech, breaking from consensus-based models.
data.description: In Krakow, Poland, and Seattle, a leading AdTech platform, CMT, has made a groundbreaking move by departing from traditional geolocation models based on consensus and instead embracing a more precise approach. This shift towards accuracy-first, evidence-driven IP data sets CMT apart as a pioneer in the industry.

data.title: Veea Inc. introduces TerraFabric at Mobile World Congress 2026, enabling AI operations at the edge efficiently. #EdgeComputing
data.description: Veea will showcase its innovative control plane for distributed edge environments at the Mobile World Congress 2026 in Barcelona from March 2 to 4. This technology is designed to help organizations with numerous deployments streamline the administration of AI workloads across their networks. It offers automated management capabilities, policy enforcement, and software lifecycle management through prpl LCM. This advancement will enable organizations to efficiently manage their fleets of devices.
